	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SPECIAL_FORCES">
			<Text>Special Forces</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_HELP_SPECIAL_FORCES">
			<Text>Late-game Infantry unit designed for rapid, powerful amphibious attacks, and supprise airial paradrops.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SPECIAL_FORCES_STRATEGY">
			<Text>Special Forces are an elite team for specilized infiltration and amphibious attacks. Special forces are an Information-Era upgrade to both the Marnine and Paratrooper units, combining both of their rolls and inheriting their abilities. Use them to stage devistating amphibious attacks, or supprise and disrupt your enemies by parradopping into enemey territory and attacking vunrable units or pillaging key resources.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_SPECIAL_FORCES_TEXT">
			<Text>Special Forces, or Special Operations Forces, are military units trained to preform unconventional missions. The elite of the elite, these units specialize in many fields, including amphibious assaults, airborne operations, counter-terrorism, espionage, sabotage, assassination, rescue, and all-around unconventional warfare. Special Forces, as they would now be recognized, emerged in the 20th century, with the outbreak of the Second World War. In 1940, the British Commandos were formed after prime minister Winston Churchill called for "specially trained troops of the hunter class, who can develop a reign of terror down the enemy coast." Today, almost a necessity for any civilization seeking military power, these units have changed wildly over the years. They've adapted and continue to adapt to the ever-changing face of warfare, proving their worth more than ever. </Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
